data.enText: a thin wire in a light bulb that produces light when electricity is passed through it
a long thin piece of sth that looks like a thread

simple_means.memory_skill: fila〔= fil〕线条 + ment 表名词 → 细线

tr: a thin wire (usually tungsten) that is heated white hot by the passage of an electric current
a threadlike structure (as a chainlike series of cells)
a very slender natural or synthetic fiber

value.def: A filament is a very thin piece or thread of something, for example the piece of wire inside a light bulb.
